(229, 207, 5, 53, 0, '10.48.2.73', 1339571254, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'P&amp;L Data Storage in plupd', '<r>P&amp;L Data Storage in plupd<br/>\nThe -U option in plupd allows storage of P&amp;L data in the dmPL_RESULTCHAR and dmPL_RESULT tables. The dmPL_RESULTCHAR stores the ‘characteristics’ of the run:<br/>\n<br/>\n <br/>\n<br/>\nCharacteristic  Description<br/>\n<br/>\nName  Identifies which dmPL_RESULT table the results will be stored in. Name is added as a field in dmPL_RESULTCHAR in V2.5e4 and up.<br/>\n<br/>\ndmResultId	Unique identifier of the data set.<br/>\n<br/>\nRunDate		Date on the report is processed (The date of Location).<br/>\n<br/>\nStartDate	Start Date of the report.<br/>\n<br/>\nEndDate		End Date of the report.<br/>\n<br/>\nCurveId		Set of curves used in the valuation of the portfolio.<br/>\n<br/>\nDescription	Comment.<br/>\n<br/>\n <br/>\nThese fields form the key for storing and retrieving data associated with a particular P&amp;L run. The dmPL_RESULT table, on the other hand, is used to store the actual P&amp;L data.<br/>\n<br/>\nIf the report is run again with -U (perhaps with different options or for different date ranges) the data in the dmPL_RESULT table are overwritten with the results produced in the last run. This means that if -U alone is used as an option, storage of multiple sets of P&amp;L results will not be possible.<br/>\n<br/>\nTo enable storage of multiple sets of P&amp;L results, the system currently offers two additional procedures that are tied with two additional options in plupd.<br/>\n<br/>\nP&amp;L Data Storage in plupd Procedures<br/>\nProcedure 1<br/>\nIn plupd, there is another option called -NOTRUNCATE . When this option is specified in conjunction with -U, the system generates unique identifiers (dmResultIds) that make the storage of multiple sets of results in the dmPL_RESULT table possible.<br/>\n<br/>\n <br/>\nProcedure 2<br/>\nA script is provided that can be used to create additional dmPL_RESULT tables with user defined extensions. (for example,. dmPL_RESULT_MTD or dmPL_RESULT_MTD_DAILY, etc.) Multiple sets of P&amp;L data can be stored in these tables once they are created via the createPNLtable.sh script. Operationally, users let the system know what table is to be updated by way of specifying the -N option together with the table extension. (for example, -N MTD or -N DAILY, etc.) Again -N option should be used in conjunction with -U.<br/>\nTo createPNLtable.sh script This script is located in the ../etc/scripts/CORE directory of the system software. In an x-term, go under this directory and type createPNLtable.sh to obtain information about the usage of the script. A DBO or SA privilege is required to run it. For more information, refer to System Administration Help.<br/>\n<br/>\n<URL url=\"http://www.summitsupport.com/docs/docs/36/userdoc/mergedProjects/core_reports/core_reports.htm#core_reports_plupd/p_l_data_storage_in_plupd.htm\"><s>[url=http://www.summitsupport.com/docs/docs/36/userdoc/mergedProjects/core_reports/core_reports.htm#core_reports_plupd/p_l_data_storage_in_plupd.htm]</s>Referenct website<e>[/url]</e></URL></r>', '06e6d0665ba6c3207638a94efc5edbd7', 0, 'EA==', 'mncx4vua', 1, 0, '', 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
(231, 209, 40, 53, 0, '10.48.2.73', 1340084081, 0, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'N201204193 fund transfer電文格式設定', '<t>fund transfer電文格式設定。<br/>\n一、新增存同：CEDELULL- HKD(22097)。<br/>\n二、當22082--&gt;22097，須發二通電文，格式如附件。<br/>\n<br/>\n修改檔案為 <br/>\n在REF53有四筆交易<br/>\n206475HK CHNY801-&gt;CITI801<br/>\n206476HK CITI801-&gt;CHNY801<br/>\n206477HK RTGS801-&gt;CDELL801<br/>\n206478HK CDELL801-&gt;RTGS801<br/>\n<br/>\n關於總行代發的部份是修改在 cCheckSendFromTPE這個FUNCTION</t>', '9fdd66bc54909b8600677c3c5f2838a7', 1, '', '17ah5hqh', 1, 1340085703, '', 53, 2, 0, 1, 0, '', 0),
